Jubilee secretary general Raphael Tuju was involved in a road accident in Nakuru. Tuju was heading to Kabarak to attend the burial of former late President Daniel ArapÂ  Moi. Tuju's vehicle hit a matatu at Magina area on the Nakuru-Nairobi highway and was admitted at Kijabe Hospital before being airlifted. He complained of chest pains before being airlifted to Nairobi in a police helicopter. Tuju was in the car with his driver and bodyguard. Sports CS Amina Mohamed was one of the first respondents on the site and helped in evacuating the secretary general. More to follow...